newsitem.title: SWITZERLAND: Swiss set terms for six-month money market claims.
newsitem.headline: Swiss set terms for six-month money market claims.

text.p: The Swiss federal government set terms on a new series 6.358 of six-month money market claims, which are to be paid for on October 31.
The issue, totaling 919.0 million Swiss francs, has an issue price of 99.168 percent, to yield 1.66 percent per annum.
The previous issue of three-month claims, paid for on October 24, raised 903.2 million francs and was priced at 99.654 percent to yield 1.374 percent annually.
